<subSubSection box="[151,1288,151,178]" pageId="6" pageNumber="498" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1288,151,178]" box="[151,1288,151,178]" pageId="6" pageNumber="498">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,1288,151,178]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="6" pageNumber="498" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,1288,151,178]" pageId="6" pageNumber="498">
2. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Grube" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[181,440,151,178]" class="Polychaeta" family="Nereididae" genus="Namalycastis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="6" pageNumber="498" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="abiuma">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[181,440,151,178]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="498">Namalycastis abiuma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Annelida, Nereidiformia) and 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[835,938,151,178]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="498">Epistylis</emphasis>
sp.2 (Ciliophora, Sessillida)
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="498" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,223,466]" pageId="6" pageNumber="498">
The present is the first record of epibionts attached to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Grube" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[751,993,223,249]" class="Polychaeta" family="Nereididae" genus="Namalycastis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="6" pageNumber="498" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="abiuma">
<emphasis box="[751,993,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="498">Namalycastis abiuma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
polychaetes. Out of 
<specimenCount box="[1223,1375,223,249]" pageId="6" pageNumber="498" type="generic">20 specimens</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Grube" baseAuthorityYear="1872" class="Polychaeta" family="Nereididae" genus="Namalycastis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="6" pageNumber="498" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="abiuma">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="498">N. abiuma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
examined, seven had individuals of 
<taxonomicName box="[644,794,259,285]" class="Oligohymenophorea" family="Epistylididae" genus="Epistylis" kingdom="Chromista" order="Peritrichida" pageId="6" pageNumber="498" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="undefined-2">
<emphasis box="[644,740,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="498">Epistylis</emphasis>
sp.2
</taxonomicName>
attached to the parapodia, mostly on dorsal cirri, but also present on the ligules and ventral cirri. The ciliates are restricted to the parapodia, not occurring either on dorsal or ventral body surfaces of the worms, and may occur on both sides, anterior and posterior, of ligules and cirri. Partially contracted mature individuals of 
<taxonomicName box="[524,674,367,393]" class="Oligohymenophorea" family="Epistylididae" genus="Epistylis" kingdom="Chromista" order="Peritrichida" pageId="6" pageNumber="498" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="undefined-2">
<emphasis box="[524,620,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="498">Epistylis</emphasis>
sp.2
</taxonomicName>
are 51.06 µm long, in average, and juveniles are 34.57 µm long, in average, in 30 individuals measured (
<figureCitation box="[563,684,403,430]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[212,1376,597,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-165@5.[212,1376,597,1851]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Specimens of Epistylis sp.2 on Namalycastis abiuma. (A). Entire worm, dorsal view; (B). Colony of Epistylis sp.2 on parapodial dorsal cirrus; (C). Solitary Epistylis sp.2 on parapodial dorsal cirrus; (D). Premature juvenile Epistylis sp. 2, on parapodial ventral cirrus; most specimens measured along longitudinal axis. White arrow points to folds of the posterior region of zooid; yellow arrow points to projecting tube formed by constriction of the peristomial lip, red arrow points to macronucleus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5726371" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5726371/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="498">Fig. 3B, D</figureCitation>
). Members of 
<taxonomicName box="[843,991,403,429]" class="Oligohymenophorea" family="Epistylididae" genus="Epistylis" kingdom="Chromista" order="Peritrichida" pageId="6" pageNumber="498" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="undefined-2">
<emphasis box="[843,939,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="498">Epistylis</emphasis>
sp.2
</taxonomicName>
were found in both solitary and colonial forms (
<figureCitation box="[232,354,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[212,1376,597,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-165@5.[212,1376,597,1851]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Specimens of Epistylis sp.2 on Namalycastis abiuma. (A). Entire worm, dorsal view; (B). Colony of Epistylis sp.2 on parapodial dorsal cirrus; (C). Solitary Epistylis sp.2 on parapodial dorsal cirrus; (D). Premature juvenile Epistylis sp. 2, on parapodial ventral cirrus; most specimens measured along longitudinal axis. White arrow points to folds of the posterior region of zooid; yellow arrow points to projecting tube formed by constriction of the peristomial lip, red arrow points to macronucleus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5726371" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5726371/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="498">Fig. 3B–D</figureCitation>
), on average ~75 individuals per worm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
